                        <h3 class = "header-spacing">Tomato-Mint Quinoa Salad</h3>
                    </div>

                        <p class = "p-spacing">Even for non-vegetarians, quinoa is a great change to rice or pasta. Quinoa provides all 9 essential amino acids, making it a complete protein. Quinoa is a gluten-free and cholesterol-free whole grain, and is almost always organic.</p>

              </div>
              <div class = "thumbnail">
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3>Preparation Instructions
                        </h3>
                        <em>Total Time: 2 hours</em>
                    </div>

              <ol class = "preparation-instructions">
                  <li>
                   Bring water to boil in a small saucepan. Pour in quinoa, raisins, and a pinch of salt. Cover, and let simmer for 12 to 15 minutes, then remove from heat, and allow to cool to room temperature.
                  </li>
                  <li>Toss together the tomatoes, onion, radish, cucumber, and almonds in a large bowl. Stir in the cooled quinoa, then season with mint, parsley, cumin, lime juice, sesame oil, and salt. Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.</li>
                  
                </ol>

